                            <comment id="14263742" author="njiang" created="Sun, 4 Jan 2015 03:34:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Krzysztof,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just checked the code history, the code that you removed was introduced since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-1689&quot; title=&quot;JMS-Headers are ignored in Producer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-1689&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-1689&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and I found the out message message id is set in the ReplyManagerSupport.processReply() method which relates to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-6218&quot; title=&quot;TransferExchage InOut ActiveMQ Exception&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-6218&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-6218&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should be safe to remove the code to avoid the race condition (if the response message comes later, the removed the code does nothing as the out message is not set yet.)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14263776" author="njiang" created="Sun, 4 Jan 2015 07:07:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied the patch into camel master, camel-2.14.x and camel-2.13.x branches with thanks to Krzystof.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
